<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="modest-adj">modest <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'mɒdɪst/    美 /'mɑːdɪst/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>谦虚的；谦逊的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Wherever you go, do be modest and honest.
无论到哪里，务必要谦虚、诚实。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>不太大的；不太贵的</strong></h4>
<p>not very great, big or expensive：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a modest price 
适中的价格</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has saved a modest amount of money. 
她攒了一小笔钱。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The living quarters are modest, with few luxuries, but cosy.
住处规模不大，也不奢华，但很舒适。</p></div></div>